</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
<p><strong>Anomalous:</strong> Any object that has been appraised by the Foundation as not meriting further study or special containment. Some of these objects may be catalogued in the <a href="/log-of-anomalous-items">Log of Anomalous Items</a>. Note: No object with an SCP designation is categorized as Anomalous, but some SCP objects were <em>once</em> categorized as Anomalous before being assigned an SCP designation.</p>
<p><strong>Neutralized:</strong> Any object that has since been destroyed, or in some way has no odd, extra-dimensional, or adverse effects. Objects classified under this class should have a note stating what class it was while it was an active SCP. The list of Neutralized SCPs can be found on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/system:page-tags/tag/neutralized#pages">Neutralized</a> page.</p>
<p>Top 10 Neutralized articles:</p>
